<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="20">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="20">
Several studies have been published detailing the osteology of various gobioid genera (e.g. Birdsong, 1975, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:44046A17-7637-4AF9-9121-F993672528FB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Microgobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Microgobius Bleeker 1931:101" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microgobius</taxonomicName>
; Gill and Hoese, 1993, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC942E77-4BCF-4808-B203-079B5AD40587" class="Actinopterygii" family="Xenisthmidae" genus="Paraxenisthmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Paraxenisthmus Gill &amp; Hoese 1993:1049" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paraxenisthmus</taxonomicName>
; Mesterman and Zander, 1984, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:962D6D5B-9370-4495-909C-BF4EBA0347E3" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Pomatoschistus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pomatoschistus Gill 1863:263" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pomatoschistus</taxonomicName>
- but including only the caudal structure of the vertebral column; Miller, 1973, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:5B83D31B-D819-4612-84D7-4292A4AD1E71" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rhyacichthyidae" genus="Rhyacichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rhyacichthys Boulenger 1901:267" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rhyacichthys</taxonomicName>
; Murdy, 1985, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B4775FB1-1EEA-4094-8B02-67113E4566AC" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Istigobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Istigobius Gobius Whitley 1932:301" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Istigobius</taxonomicName>
; Springer, 1988, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:047CDC40-9B25-478C-81A9-A94D7161E89A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Xenisthmidae" genus="Rotuma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rotuma Springer 1988:531" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rotuma</taxonomicName>
). A much larger number of publications deal with selected osteological features of these fishes; these are often comparative in nature and aimed at elucidating phylogenetic relationships (e.g. Akihito, 1963, 1967, 1969, 1971; Birdsong et al., 1988; Harrison, 1989; Larson, 2001; Murdy, 1989; Pezold, 1993; Scsepka et al., 1999; Springer, 1983; Winterbottom, 1990).
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageNumber="21" pageNumber="20">
Birdsong et al. (1988) placed 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trimma</taxonomicName>
in their 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C48B727-4D21-4F6F-98E7-81332480FC17" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Priolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Priolepis Valenciennes &amp; Ehrenberg 1837:67" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Priolepis</taxonomicName>
Group, a large assemblage of genera the species of which dominate the coral reefs of the Indo-Pacific. This group is defined by a dorsal pterygiophore formula of 3-22110, 26 vertebrae, a single epural and two anal fin pterygiophores anterior to the first haemal spine. The only taxon belonging to this assemblage for which all components of the osteology are described is 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Istigobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ornatus">Istigobius ornatus (Murdy, 1985)</taxonomicName>
. Pezold’ s (1993) study of the monophyly of the Gobiinae, based on the oculoscapular pore configurations, unfortunately cannot be applied to certain genera currently assigned to those members of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C48B727-4D21-4F6F-98E7-81332480FC17" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Priolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Priolepis Valenciennes &amp; Ehrenberg 1837:67" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Priolepis</taxonomicName>
group which lack this structural complex - as Pezold noted. These include the “type” genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C48B727-4D21-4F6F-98E7-81332480FC17" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Priolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Priolepis Valenciennes &amp; Ehrenberg 1837:67" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Priolepis</taxonomicName>
, as well as 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trimma</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:03E74533-3222-4BD6-8DA9-D6100460EC51" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimmatom" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimmatom Winterbottom &amp; Emery 1981:140" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trimmatom</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F888ECBB-D893-412A-A4B0-73F1DB710EA9" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Paratrimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Paratrimma Hoese &amp; Brothers 1976:495" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Paratrimma</taxonomicName>
. It should be noted that the 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3C48B727-4D21-4F6F-98E7-81332480FC17" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Priolepis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Priolepis Valenciennes &amp; Ehrenberg 1837:67" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Priolepis</taxonomicName>
group itself may not form a monophyletic assemblage. For example, both Thacker and Cole (2002) and Thacker (2003) conclude from studies of DNA sequences that the two species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:05DF0C27-AACC-474E-AE80-1145F50218A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Fusigobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Fusigobius Whitley 1930:122" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Fusigobius</taxonomicName>
they examined, 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Fusigobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neophytus">F. neophytus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:BB8AAD92-EA27-4865-9B14-19F38B6B1007" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Fusigobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Fusigobius signipinnis Hoese &amp; Obika 1988:282" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="signipinnis">F. signipinnis</taxonomicName>
, belong in very different lineages. Note also that the issue of non-monophyly of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:05DF0C27-AACC-474E-AE80-1145F50218A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Fusigobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Fusigobius Whitley 1930:122" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Fusigobius</taxonomicName>
itself was not specifically addressed by Thacker and Cole (2002), who stated that resolution of this issue would have to await revisionary studies of the species currently assigned to that genus. However, they did demonstrate that neither species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:05DF0C27-AACC-474E-AE80-1145F50218A6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Fusigobius" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Fusigobius Whitley 1930:122" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Fusigobius</taxonomicName>
was particularly closely related to 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:54C6C567-7345-422F-9A0F-88BDDFDF260A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Coryphopterus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Coryphopterus Gill 1863:262" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="20" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Coryphopterus</taxonomicName>
, as maintained by Randall (1995).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="21">
Within 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trimma</taxonomicName>
(itself not currently strongly defensible as a monophyletic assemblage even with the inclusion of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:03E74533-3222-4BD6-8DA9-D6100460EC51" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimmatom" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimmatom Winterbottom &amp; Emery 1981:140" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Trimmatom</taxonomicName>
- see Winterbottom, 1990), null hypotheses can nevertheless be erected for two apparently monophyletic subsets. One of these is the 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C32FF53C-499C-46C3-972E-3139AB79174A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimma caesiura Jordan &amp; Seale 1906:391" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caesiura">Trimma caesiura</taxonomicName>
complex, defined by a very steep-sided trench between the orbits that continues around the posterodorsal margins of the eye (see Winterbottom and Villa, in press, for a list of nominal species included and a more detailed description and illustrations of these structures); the other is the 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:994C8E55-200A-4D11-8C45-1F8633E9CF8C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimma tevegae Cohen &amp; Davis 1969:321" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tevegae">T. tevegae</taxonomicName>
complex (nominal species: 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:994C8E55-200A-4D11-8C45-1F8633E9CF8C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimma tevegae Cohen &amp; Davis 1969:321" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tevegae">T. tevegae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FC288AAA-A102-419A-AFE0-CBB14758596C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimma taylori Lobel 1979:3" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="taylori">T. taylori</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AA0320C2-3C9E-4000-8EEA-EB72CB6E764F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimma hoesei Winterbottom 1984:704" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hoesei">T. hoesei</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C1D89FBC-8B7D-42F8-8BCC-19220AA0D133" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimma griffithsi Winterbottom 1984:701" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griffithsi">T. griffithsi</taxonomicName>
and probably 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:B830046C-B336-4993-8C54-8AA1365A7F9A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimma winchi Winterbottom 1984:712" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="winchi">T. winchi</taxonomicName>
), defined by a much broader, flat, bony interorbital region, a better developed rostral cartilage, extensive bony contact between the posteroventral process of the symplectic and the anterodorsal process of the preopercle, and greatly expanded haemal canals in the first few caudal vertebrae (see figs. 26 and 27 in Winterbottom, 1984, of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:FC288AAA-A102-419A-AFE0-CBB14758596C" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimma taylori Lobel 1979:3" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="taylori">Trimma taylori</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:C1D89FBC-8B7D-42F8-8BCC-19220AA0D133" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Trimma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Trimma griffithsi Winterbottom 1984:701" order="Perciformes" pageNumber="21" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griffithsi">T. griffithsi</taxonomicName>
respectively). There are numerous undescribed new species in both of these complexes.
</paragraph>
